<plot>The average city dweller has lived about thirty plus years of life. In those thirty plus years, is an accumulated storage of far too many memories. Of which the strongest ones are those with indelible moments of sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and touch. Two people fall in love through a shared commonality, but never meet. A mother fantasizes over her son's best friend. A young girl sprays cologne over common household items. A man develops a palate for his mother's goldfish. A girl follows a limping stranger around a city.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?006280</url></doc>
